  "body": "Let me preface this by saying that I'm not a dev, so assuming this is feasible from a dev standpoint...\r\n\r\nUnder the \"View and Send\" tab, the UI should prompt/encourage/highlight using Metamask if the user's wallet is already unlocked via Metamask.\r\n\r\nGive the opportunity to \"Unlock without Metamask\", which leads the user to the other options. \r\n\r\nUser Story:\r\nAs a user that has Metamask installed, \r\nAnd I currently have a wallet unlocked,\r\nMyCrypto should \"highlight\" Metamask as the primary method for accessing my wallet,\r\nSo that I am safely accessing my wallet\r\n\r\n<img width=\"1438\" alt=\"screen shot 2018-04-25 at 10 07 10 am\" src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/23407603/39261165-7e1b172a-4870-11e8-8dc3-286c76bab1cd.png\">",
